Apache Status Plugin
======================

Created by Hampton Catlin
Modifications and documentation by Josh Nichols and Jesse Newland

Overview
--------

Reports data collected from from mod_status:

* The number of worker serving requests
* The number of idle worker
* A total number of accesses and byte count served (*)
* The time the server was started/restarted and the time it has been running for
* Averages giving the number of requests per second, the number of bytes served per second and the average number of bytes per request (*)
* The current percentage CPU used in total by Apache (*)

The lines marked "(*)" are only available if ExtendedStatus is On.

See the mod_status docs for more details:

http://httpd.apache.org/docs/2.0/mod/mod_status.html